    Scope and Contents
MENTAL HEALTH CARE PROJECT 
Bushnell, manager of the clothing department at Jacksonville State Hospital, discusses changes within the clothing and inventory departments, in staff uniforms, employee benefits, hiring practices, treatments for mental disorders and in the services offered by the hospital. He also recalls living conditions for employees on the hospital grounds. 1 tape, 60 mins., 21 pp. 
Interview by Rodger Streitmatter, 1972 
